metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #384
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #809
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: stacks #57
metadata.description:
An exploration of vernacular architectural forms and combinatorial logics. If the roof form is typically what gives a building its character (i.e., its primary reading in a public-facing elevation), we can play with those proportions to achieve a particular reading. Square proportions become domestic, while shallower gables suggest more industrial typologies, narrower ones may even feel religious. Mixing a variety of proportions together allow for a proto-urban cacophony of elevational readings. These generative compositions play with both existing perceptions of the built environment as well as imaginary potentials of future architectures to come.

As impossible as these compositions may seem, they are fully realized as 3D forms, extruded at various lengths, all connected to a fictional “ground”. They are rendered using an elevation oblique projection, a form of parallel projection that visually distorts the geometry to show accurate depth and a true frontal elevation.

Press 's' in live mode to save a PNG.

metadata.name: guided meditation #10
metadata.description:
🔊🔊🔊

epilepsy warning: pulsing colors

our culture, society and environment is evermore challenging our collective mental health. Do we modify our path or find ways to cope? is technology assisting in this adaptation or is it a driving force of turbulence?

text-to-speech voice is generated from a neural network trained on meditation scripts

variations:

- mantra (1/200): pre-generated, uncurated audio voice loops. Between 20—70 seconds each, 2 hours total
- room (1/2): the room determines the background and sound dynamics
- instrument (1/3): sound signifying the start and end of the meditation
- color (∞): color is the combination of 3 randomly generated light sources
- shape (∞): shape is generated by random variations of a tours knot
- special (~2%): shape is iridescent

click - play/pause
drag - rotate room

iphone: may not loop automatically, just tap to restart

no tokens will be burned from this series

when all tokens are minted, they will be displayed on a dedicated website

metadata.name: polygonism #1
metadata.description:
Back to the basics of geometric generative art, this work generates double pursuit ngons in different styles and based on the number of points in the ngon.

This piece is inspired by the work of Jos Vromans.

Controls:
* Press "s" to save the current image

Features:
* alpha: determines the color alpha value
* palette: 33 possible variations of sets of 4 colours
* points: number of points in the ngon
* strokeWeight: determines line thickness


Made in Zoutleeuw, Belgium by Gorik with p5

metadata.name: Texture pattern I  #15
metadata.description:
"Texture pattern" is an experiment about achieving colours with small lines forming a texture that you can alter. The piece is based on a grid system that is altered by a factor and in orientation, 3 mathematical sequences create a base rhythm. 

The colour palette is inspired by Riley's "La fête" with modifications and the monochrome version is based on 2 blacks and 2 whites.

In the live version, you can interact with your token using the following keys

's' saves a jpg
'1','2','3','4' sets the pixel density to 1,2,3,4
'+' adds 1000 lines per rectangle
'-' removes 1000 lines per rectangle
'n' allows you to toggle extra noise
'm' adds more noise
'b' removes some noise
'0' to toggle the background of each rectangle
